.SH "Detailed Description"
.PP 
This interface offers ways to convert between hwloc cpusets and glibc cpusets such as those manipulated by sched_getaffinity() or pthread_attr_setaffinity_np()\&.

.PP
\fBNote\fP
.RS 4
Topology \fRtopology\fP must match the current machine\&. 
.RE
.PP

.SH "Function Documentation"
.PP 
.SS "int hwloc_cpuset_from_glibc_sched_affinity (\fBhwloc_topology_t\fP topology, \fBhwloc_cpuset_t\fP hwlocset, const cpu_set_t * schedset, size_t schedsetsize)\fR [inline]\fP"

.PP
Convert glibc sched affinity CPU set \fRschedset\fP into hwloc CPU set\&. This function may be used before calling sched_setaffinity or any other function that takes a cpu_set_t as input parameter\&.

.PP
\fRschedsetsize\fP should be sizeof(cpu_set_t) unless \fRschedset\fP was dynamically allocated with CPU_ALLOC

.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
0 on success\&. 

.PP
-1 with errno set to \fRENOMEM\fP if some internal reallocation failed\&. 
.RE
.PP

.SS "int hwloc_cpuset_to_glibc_sched_affinity (\fBhwloc_topology_t\fP topology, \fBhwloc_const_cpuset_t\fP hwlocset, cpu_set_t * schedset, size_t schedsetsize)\fR [inline]\fP"

.PP
Convert hwloc CPU set \fRtoposet\fP into glibc sched affinity CPU set \fRschedset\fP\&. This function may be used before calling sched_setaffinity or any other function that takes a cpu_set_t as input parameter\&.

.PP
\fRschedsetsize\fP should be sizeof(cpu_set_t) unless \fRschedset\fP was dynamically allocated with CPU_ALLOC

.PP
\fBReturns\fP
.RS 4
0\&. 
.RE
.PP

